		<div class="b center">With no duplicates in the feed!</div>
	</li>
</ol>

<p>So, that is the basic method behind posting to a group.</p>
<p>A few more pointers and tips:</p>

<ul>
	<li>
		Your name will be added to the front of your tweet (along with a colon and a space), so make sure to leave room - you can't post a
		full 140 characters. If your username is 11 characters long (like mine), your message to the group can only be 127 characters long
		(11 for username + 2 for the colon and space + message).
	</li>
	<li>
		If you want to tweet "at" someone in the group using the @ reply method, make sure you still start with the ReTweetBot group name
		first, otherwise it won't post. Saying "@predfans @pwnicholson blah blah" <span class="i">will</span> post to the group. Saying
		"@pwnicholson @predfans blah blah" <span class="i">will not</span> post to the group.
	</li>
	<li>
		Same principle aplies to DM posting method. "d predfans @pwnicholson blah blah" will post to the group just fine. "d pwnicholson
		@predfans blah blah" or "d pwnicholson predfans blah blah" will not post to the group.
	</li>
</ul>

